<subSubSection id="C33380D6FFFC780AC181E72C28CCFB1B" pageId="9" pageNumber="563" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B96D35DFFFC780AC181E72C28CCFB1B" blockId="9.[151,1437,1050,1183]" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis id="B95D0F4FFFFC780AC181E72C2B6AFBB7" bold="true" box="[151,273,1050,1075]" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C29A8DEFFFC780AC0A4E72D284BFBB7" authorityName="Danilov" authorityYear="2017" box="[434,560,1051,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" genus="Podalonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kazenasi">
<emphasis id="B95D0F4FFFFC780AC0A4E72D284BFBB7" box="[434,560,1051,1075]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">P. kazenasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C29A8DEFFFC780AC218E72D2E75FBB7" authority="(Kohl, 1901)" authorityName="Kohl" authorityYear="1901" baseAuthorityName="Kohl" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[782,1038,1050,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" genus="Podalonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minax">
<emphasis id="B95D0F4FFFFC780AC218E72D2916FBB6" box="[782,877,1051,1074]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">P. minax</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB8AEACFFFC780AC295E72C2E7DFBB7" author="Kohl" box="[899,1030,1050,1075]" pageId="9" pageNumber="563" refString="Kohl, F. F. (1901) Zur Kenntnis der Sandwespen (Gen. Ammophila Kirby). Annalen des k. k. Naturhistorischen Hofmuseums, 16, 142 - 164." type="journal article" year="1901">Kohl, 1901</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in having red legs and a glabrous propodeal enclosure, but differs by the simple clypeus, and by the shape of penis valve (as in figs 71–73) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C29A8DEFFFC780AC491E7092AA0FBFE" baseAuthorityName="Kohl" baseAuthorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" genus="Podalonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minax">
<emphasis id="B95D0F4FFFFC780AC491E7092AA0FBFE" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">P. minax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the clypeus is acute apically, and the penis valve is simple). It differs from all the other species with a glabrous propodeal enclosure in having red legs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF5683D5FFFC780AC181E4952EC7F85E" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893852/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="563" targetBox="[155,1432,1240,1925]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="8B96D35DFFFC780AC181E4952EC7F85E" blockId="9.[151,1435,1955,2010]" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis id="B95D0F4FFFFC780AC181E4952B22F83D" bold="true" box="[151,345,1955,1977]" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">FIGURES 66–73.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C29A8DEFFFC780AC073E4952848F83D" authority="Danilov, 2017" authorityName="Danilov" authorityYear="2017" box="[357,563,1955,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" genus="Podalonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kazenasi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B95D0F4FFFFC780AC073E4952848F83D" box="[357,563,1955,1977]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">Podalonia kazenasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26EB234FFFC780AC329E4952805F83D" box="[575,638,1955,1977]" pageId="9" pageNumber="563" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B95D0F4FFFFC780AC329E4952805F83D" bold="true" box="[575,638,1955,1977]" pageId="9" pageNumber="563">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Holotype ♂: 66—general view, labels; 67—face; 68—head lateral; 69— mesosoma lateral; 70—mesonotum; 71—genitalia ventral; 72—genitalia dorsal; 73—penis valve lateral.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C33380D6FFFF7809C1D1E3A12BD9FDB9" pageId="10" pageNumber="564" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B96D35DFFFF7809C1D1E3A128F5FD9C" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis id="B95D0F4FFFFF7809C1D1E3A12BD0FF34" bold="true" box="[199,427,151,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity id="4CD17EB8FFFF7809C34CE3AE28C9FF2B" box="[602,690,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="10" pageNumber="564" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B95D0F4FFFFF7809C3D2E3AE297AFF34" box="[708,769,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">Head</emphasis>
. Clypeus slightly elongate and concave; apical margin emarginated. Clypeus, subantennal sclerite, and frons with dense appressed silvery setae. Vertex, occiput, and gena microsculptured, with irregular punctures; gena with appressed silvery setae. Erect setae pale. Mandible black with red spots medially. Palpi red. Small spot on scape red. 
<emphasis id="B95D0F4FFFFF7809C20BE23329EEFE98" box="[797,917,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">Mesosoma</emphasis>
with pale erect setae. Pronotum and scutum finely rugose, more or less shiny, with sparse, appressed silvery setae. Mesosoma laterally and ventrally with dense appressed silvery setae except upper metapleural area with sparse setae. Propodeum finely punctatorugose. Propodeal enclosure glabrous, finely obliquely striate. Tegula red. 
<emphasis id="B95D0F4FFFFF7809C281E24629A1FE03" box="[919,986,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">Wings</emphasis>
hyaline, with slightly darker spot near marginal cell; veins brown; costal vein dark brown to black. 
<emphasis id="B95D0F4FFFFF7809C258E2A329F8FE28" box="[846,899,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">Legs</emphasis>
red, except black coxae and partly dark brown hind tarsi. Claws without subbasal tooth. Spines red, dark on hind tarsi. 
<emphasis id="B95D0F4FFFFF7809C2C4E28F2E3CFE54" box="[978,1095,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">Metasoma</emphasis>
all red except dark brown T7 and S7 and except black petiole. Penis valve in lateral view crescent-like, with teeth at inner margin; in ventral view without transverse spines (
<figureCitation id="1312CFD8FFFF7809C0E8E2C928F9FD9C" box="[510,642,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 66 – 73" captionStartId="9.[151,263,1955,1977]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,1240,1925]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,1236,1934]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 66 – 73. Podalonia kazenasi sp. n. Holotype ♂: 66 — general view, labels; 67 — face; 68 — head lateral; 69 — mesosoma lateral; 70 — mesonotum; 71 — genitalia ventral; 72 — genitalia dorsal; 73 — penis valve lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/893852/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">Figs 71–73</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96D35DFFFF7809C1D1E1122BD9FDB9" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,717]" box="[199,418,548,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis id="B95D0F4FFFFF7809C1D1E1122B5EFDB9" bold="true" box="[199,293,548,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="564">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
